# Angular 20 with PrimeNG - Cursor AI Rules

## Core Angular 20 Rules

### Components
- Always use standalone components (no NgModules)
- Use signals for state: `signal()`, `computed()`
- Use `input()` and `output()` functions (NOT `@Input`/`@Output` decorators)
- Use `inject()` for dependency injection (NOT constructor injection)
- OnPush change detection required on ALL components: `changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`
- Import components/directives/pipes directly in `@Component` imports array

### Templates
- Use `@if` (NOT `*ngIf`)
- Use `@for` with track (NOT `*ngFor`)
- Use `@switch` (NOT `*ngSwitch`)
- Use `[class.x]="condition()"` (NOT `[ngClass]`)
- Use `[style.x]="value()"` (NOT `[ngStyle]`)
- Always include `track` in `@for` loops for performance

### State Management
- Use signals for all reactive state
- Use `computed()` for derived state
- Update signals with `.update()` or `.set()` (NEVER `.mutate()`)
- Example: `this.count.update(value => value + 1)`

### Services
- All services must have `providedIn: 'root'`
- Use `inject()` function instead of constructor injection
- Use signals for service state
- Example: `private http = inject(HttpClient);`

### Routing
- Use lazy loading with `loadComponent()` or `loadChildren()`
- Use functional guards (NOT class-based)
- Example: `const authGuard = (): boolean => inject(AuthService).isAuthenticated();`

## PrimeNG Components

### Usage
- Import PrimeNG components as standalone
- Example: `import { ButtonModule } from 'primeng/button';`
- Add to component imports: `imports: [ButtonModule, InputTextModule]`
- Refer to https://primeng.org for component API
- Common components: Button, InputText, Table, Dialog, Card, Dropdown, Calendar

### Styling PrimeNG
- PrimeNG components work seamlessly with Tailwind utility classes
- Use `class` attribute for Tailwind utilities
- Use `styleClass` for PrimeNG component-specific styling
- Example: `<p-button label="Click" styleClass="w-full" class="mb-4" />`

## Tailwind CSS (if enabled)

### Utilities
- Use Tailwind utility classes for layout and spacing
- Responsive design: `md:grid-cols-2`, `lg:flex-row`
- Dark mode (if configured): `dark:bg-gray-900`, `dark:text-white`
- With tailwindcss-primeui: Use design tokens like `bg-primary`, `text-primary`

### Best Practices
- Prefer utilities over custom CSS
- Use `@apply` in SCSS only for repeated patterns
- Keep component templates clean with utility classes

## Folder Structure

### New Features
- Create in `src/app/features/{feature-name}/`
- Structure: `components/`, `models/`, `pages/`, `services/`
- Feature routes in `{feature-name}.routes.ts`

### Core Services
- Singleton services → `src/app/core/services/`
- Guards → `src/app/core/guards/`
- Interceptors → `src/app/core/interceptors/`
- Models → `src/app/core/models/`

### Shared Components
- Reusable components → `src/app/shared/components/`
- Directives → `src/app/shared/directives/`
- Pipes → `src/app/shared/pipes/`
- Utils → `src/app/shared/utils/`

## Code Patterns

### Component Template
```typescript
import { Component, signal, computed, input, output, ChangeDetectionStrategy } from '@angular/core';
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';
import { ButtonModule } from 'primeng/button';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-example',
  imports: [CommonModule, ButtonModule],
  templateUrl: './example.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./example.component.scss'],
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
})
export class ExampleComponent {
  readonly title = input.required<string>();
  readonly itemSelected = output<Item>();

  readonly count = signal(0);
  readonly doubled = computed(() => this.count() * 2);

  increment(): void {
    this.count.update(n => n + 1);
  }
}
```

### Service Template
```typescript
import { Injectable, inject, signal } from '@angular/core';
import { HttpClient } from '@angular/common/http';

@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })
export class DataService {
  private readonly http = inject(HttpClient);
  private readonly data = signal<Item[]>([]);

  readonly items = computed(() => this.data());

  loadItems(): void {
    this.http.get<Item[]>('/api/items')
      .subscribe(items => this.data.set(items));
  }
}
```

### Template with Control Flow
```html
@if (loading()) {
  <p-progressSpinner />
} @else if (error()) {
  <p-message severity="error" [text]="error()" />
} @else {
  @for (item of items(); track item.id) {
    <p-card [header]="item.name">
      {{ item.description }}
    </p-card>
  } @empty {
    <p>No items found</p>
  }
}
```

### Functional Guard
```typescript
import { inject } from '@angular/core';
import { Router } from '@angular/router';

export const authGuard = (): boolean => {
  const authService = inject(AuthService);
  const router = inject(Router);

  if (authService.isAuthenticated()) {
    return true;
  }

  router.navigate(['/login']);
  return false;
};
```

## File Naming

- Components: `user-list.component.ts`
- Services: `auth.service.ts`
- Guards: `auth.guard.ts`
- Pipes: `date-format.pipe.ts`
- Directives: `highlight.directive.ts`
- Models: `user.model.ts`

## Testing

### Component Tests
```typescript
import { ComponentFixture, TestBed } from '@angular/core/testing';
import { ExampleComponent } from './example.component';

describe('ExampleComponent', () => {
  let component: ExampleComponent;
  let fixture: ComponentFixture<ExampleComponent>;

  beforeEach(async () => {
    await TestBed.configureTestingModule({
      imports: [ExampleComponent]
    }).compileComponents();

    fixture = TestBed.createComponent(ExampleComponent);
    component = fixture.componentInstance;
    fixture.detectChanges();
  });

  it('should create', () => {
    expect(component).toBeTruthy();
  });

  it('should increment counter', () => {
    expect(component.count()).toBe(0);
    component.increment();
    expect(component.count()).toBe(1);
  });
});
```

## ESLint Rules

- ❌ NO `@Input()` / `@Output()` → Use `input()` / `output()`
- ❌ NO `*ngIf` / `*ngFor` / `*ngSwitch` → Use `@if` / `@for` / `@switch`
- ❌ NO constructor injection → Use `inject()`
- ❌ NO direct signal mutation → Use `.set()` / `.update()`
- ✅ ALWAYS use `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`
- ✅ ALWAYS use signals for component state
- ✅ ALWAYS use `readonly` for signals and computed
- ✅ ALWAYS use standalone components

